genresAdvancedInfo.name: italian occult psychedelia
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Italian occult psychedelia is a subgenre of psychedelic rock that emerged in the late 1960s and early 1970s. It is characterized by its use of mystical and occult themes, as well as its experimental soundscapes and improvisational style. The music often features heavy use of reverb, echo, and other effects to create a dreamlike and otherworldly atmosphere.
